<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on CIS Leaders Summit 15 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on CIS Leaders Summit 15 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Spokesman Terms Summit `Successful' </H4>

<F P=102> LD1504130394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1222 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1504130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Anna Melnikova and Gennadiy </F>
Yezhov] 
  [Text] Moscow April 15 TASS -- "The CIS summit, which is 
about to end here, can already be described as successful," 
presidential press secretary Vyacheslav Kostikov told a press 
conference at "President-Hotel" here today. He noted that the 
successful solution of the problem of guarding the external 
borders of the CIS testified to a new understanding of the idea 
of the commonwealth's unity. "It can already be said that we are 
nearing the finishing line. A joint memorandum on the 
participation of CIS members in the protection of the external 
borders in the Central Asian region and also a memorandum on the 
protection of external borders with Ukraine and Belarus has 
already been signed. Corresponding documents are ready to be 
signed." 
  "Thus," Kostikov said, "the system of a single guarded 
border 
is being restored. Moldova is expected to join this memorandum." 
  Asked about Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev's 
initiative to set up a Euro-Asian Union, Kostikov said with 
certainty: "As far as I known, this problem was not raised in 
any of the speeches as it was formulated by the Kazakh 
president." 
  Kostikov said that President Yeltsin rounded off the summit 
meeting by saying: "Let's take upon ourselves as much 
cooperation as it is in the interests of our states." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

