<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on CIS Leaders Summit 15 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on CIS Leaders Summit 15 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    CIS Organizational Changes Approved </H4>

<F P=102> LD1504191794 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1700 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The present summit introduced several innovations to 
the organizational structure of the CIS. Leaders of CIS 
coordinating bodies -- Vladimir Shumeyko, chairman of the 
Interparliamentary Assembly, Defense Council Chairman Pavel 
Grachev, Andrey Kozyrev, chairman of the Foreign Affairs 
Council, and Andrey Nikolayev, chairman of the Council of 
Commanders of CIS Countries' Border Troops -- took part in its 
work for the first time. A one-year term was set today for the 
rotation of the leaders of the statutory bodies of the CIS. 
This means that Boris Yeltsin and Viktor Chernomyrdin will 
continue to carry out the functions of chairman of the Council 
of Heads of State and chairman of the Council of Heads of 
Government until 31 December 1994. The CIS heads of state also 
approved the symbols -- the flag and emblem -- of the 
Commonwealth of Independent States, viewing this graphic image 
as a powerful and developing tree, a chalice bringing people 
light and warmth, and wings of birds in a single formation. The 
next meeting will, therefore, be held under the sky blue flag of 
the CIS. That meeting is scheduled to take place on 9 
September. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

