<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on CIS Leaders Summit 15 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on CIS Leaders Summit 15 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Leaders Comment on Eurasian Union </H4>

<F P=102> LD1504165594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1404 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1504165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 15 TASS -- An initiative to create a 
Euro-Asian union put forward by Kazakh President Nursultan 
Nazarbayev has evoked strong interest among journalists. 
However, according to Boris Yeltsin, the idea of the Euro-Asian 
Union was not discussed at the CIS summit on Friday since Kazakh 
President Nursultan Nazarbayev was not present at the session 
because he was unwell and no concrete information on this 
problem was available. 
  According to Kazakh Vice-President Erik Esanbayev [name as 
received], who led the Kazakh delegation to the CIS summit, the 
idea of the formation of the Euro-Asian Union was suggested by 
life itself. "At present, we are watching the response to the 
idea made by politicians and the mass media," Esanbayev said, 
adding that a comprehensive programme for the formation of the 
Euro-Asian Union will be submitted by Kazakhstan at the next CIS 
summit. 
  Chairman of the Tajik Parliament, Emomali Rakhmonov, 
believes 
that the idea of the formation of the Euro-Asian union is a 
"good" one, but "the possibilities of the CIS have not been 
fully used up yet, which was confirmed once again by signatures 
of the Commonwealth presidents put under adopted documents," he 
said. 
  Uzbek President Islam Karimov shares the opinion of the 
Tajik 
parliament chairman, saying that "the idea of the Euro-Asian 
Union does not have any serious foundation whatsoever." He 
pointed that it is necessary to persistently carry through the 
idea of strengthening the CIS, primarily by enhancing economic 
integration and creating an economic union. "Therefore, it 
would not be correct to leave the matter of strengthening the 
CIS half-finished and put forward a new initiative," Karimov 
said. 
  Asked whether agreements reached by heads of the CIS have 
been efficiently fulfilled since the day of the CIS formation, 
Yeltsin said that a decision was adopted on Friday to check 
whether the discipline of carrying out these agreement was 
observed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

