<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on CIS Leaders Summit 15 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on CIS Leaders Summit 15 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Azerbaijan Seeks Dialogue With Armenia </H4>

<F P=102> LD1504190794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1854 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1504190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Shulman] </F>
  [Text] Azeri President Geydar Aliyev said here tonight he 
plans further dialogue with Armenian leader Levon Ter-Petrosyan 
but made no comments on the report claiming his meeting with 
Ter-Petrosyan in Moscow on April 16. 
  He said today's meeting with Russian President Boris Yeltsin 
focused on the search for possibilities of cease-fire and 
negotiations. 
  The Azeri demands are not excessive, said the Azeri leader. 
They include cease-fire in the conflict zone, liberation of the 
occupied Azeri lands and negotiations to discuss the status of 
Nagorno-Karabakh. 
  Aliyev is convinced that the two peoples are ready for 
cease-fire. He stressed he "has a reliable information that the 
absolute majority of Karabakh Armenians do not want to fight, 
they are forced to do it, to involve in the senseless war". 
  The bloodshed must be stopped as soon as possible to 
terminate sufferings of Azeri and Armenian mothers, and the 
Armenian and Azeri presidents must agree on this, said Aliyev. 
  He stressed he is basically not against contacts with 
Armenian representatives of Nagorno-Karabakh, however, being the 
Azeri president, do not plan to have equal negotiations with 
citizens of the state he heads. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

