<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   ITAR-TASS Carries Press Review for 16 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ITAR-TASS Carries Press Review for 16 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604062594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0544 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1604062594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Press Review" -- ITAR-TASS headline] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 16 TASS -- NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA 
(independent newspaper) on the CIS summit: 
  "The economic integration of CIS member-countries proceeds 
perhaps more successfully than the resolution of many regional 
conflicts. The fact that the bulk of the package of issues 
considered dealt with the situation in the Republic of 
Tajikistan and the Transcaucasus shows that the Russian 
Federation tries to apply all CIS instruments to somehow secure 
the powers of its troops at flashpoints and share responsibility 
with ex-Soviet republics". 
  ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI believes that "one can view as the main 
achievements of the summit the establishment of a permanently 
functioning agency -- a commission for economic union affairs -- 
at the CIS coordinating consultative committee and the signing 
of an agreement between Russia and all the CIS countries on a 
multi-sided free trade area". 
  Referring to remarks by Vladimir Mashits, Russian minister 
for cooperation, the newspaper points out: "The implementation 
of this agreement may begin soon". 
  PRAVDA on the CIS summit outcome: 
  "There were no sensations. The only more or less mature 
undertaking -- the establishment of an economic union underwent 
development. The establishment of a free trade area will 
possibly become the first step towards reunification. 
  "Thus, the vector of the movement has been chosen: to 
recreate the union, an economic one at first, and subsequently a 
Euro-Asian one." 
  KRASNAYA ZVEZDA (Red Star) carries an interview with Yuriy 
Meshkov, the first-ever president of the Republic of the Crimea. 
  In response to a question about the Crimean president's view 
of the future of the Black Sea Fleet and its status, Meshkov 
said: "The fleet should be Russian, since Ukraine is not in a 
position to maintain it... I think the Black Sea Fleet has been 
and remains the guarantor of stability in the Crimea and an 
important element of the balance of forces in the south European 
region." 
  TRUD on the birth centenary of former Soviet leader Nikita 
Khrushchov: 
  "The transformation era of Khrushchov days created a culture 
medium which brought forth people who arrived at conclusions 
about the essence of administrative socialism, its historical 
prospectlessness and the need to wind up the experiment on its 
basis and launch a quest for new principles for the life of 
millions of people". 
  RABOCHAYA TRIBUNA on Khrushchov's birth centenary: 
  "Thousands of innocent people who were subjected to 
repressions are grateful to Khrushchov for the regained freedom 
and rehabilitation. 
  "And still, under Khrushchov, we began to be dependent on 
overseas bread. Prices began to move upwards, and haphazard 
reorganisations were launched. In such affairs, associates 
recede into the background, leaving the leader confronted with 
the social discontent." 
  KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA carries an article the writer of which 
points out that, to his mind, there is still the need for a 
long, thorough and impartial analysis of everything that was 
done by Nikita Khrushchov, one of the most distinctive and 
complex politicians of the 20th century". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

