<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Criticizes Eurasian Union Idea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Criticizes Eurasian Union Idea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704160494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1230 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1704160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian ultra-nationalist Vladimir Zhirinovskiy has 
criticized Kazakhstan President Nursultan Nazarbayev's proposal 
for a Eurasian Union. Addressing a congress of the Union of 
Officers on Saturday, Zhirinovskiy warned about "the danger for 
those who are in favor of the restoration of the Soviet Union if 
they support the initiative of President Nursultan Nazarbayev." 
A community of states "with the same people -- Nazarbayev 
(Uzbekistan President Islam) Karimov, (Georgian leader Eduard) 
Shevardnadze, (Moldovan President Mircea) Snegur, and others - 
staying in their offices would be the worst that could happen," 
"a trap for many years, from which it would be difficult to 
break out," he said. 
  A "single union state" should be based on the territorial 
unification of the former Soviet republics, the merger of their 
armed forces, security services and financial systems, and 
uniform citizenship, Zhirinovskiy said. Meanwhile, "Russians 
living in regions where temporarily somebody else's flag is 
flying, have the right to self-determination," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

