<F P=106> [Video report by correspondent Sladkov, including recorded </F>
comment by Stanislav Terekhov, chairman of the Officers' Union; 
from the "Vesti" newscast] 
  [Text] [Sladkov] The Russian Power Party [Rossiyskaya 
Derzhavnaya Partiya] is the name of the new political party that 
today held the second stage of its founding conference in Moscow 
Oblast. The most active sections of the Officers' Union, the 
National Salvation Front, and of other small patriotic groupings 
were the initiators for creating the party. 
  [Terekhov] We are beginning to work differently from the 
image of being extremists both in the streets and at meetings by 
which the people had known us. We are going to defend our 
stance in a serious way not by shouting in the streets but by 
our deeds. 
  [Sladkov] According to Stanislav Terekhov, from now on the 
patriots will start nominating their candidates to all levels of 
state power as the continuation of the struggle to bring to 
power the people to whom the interests of the country are above 
everything else. Incidently, every leader always talks about 
his love for his motherland and if that leader is the supreme 
leader of the country he should be a professional. 

</TEXT>

