<H3> <TI>   Conflict at ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Conflict at ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1504125094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 15 Apr 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK1504125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report under the "In Brief" rubric] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- A conflict continues in the ROSSIYSKAYA 
GAZETA editorial office between the administration and the 
journalist collective caused by changes in the publication's 
charter and the list of members of its staff. According to a 
staffer who asked not to be identified, "in violation of the law 
on the mass media, the new charter of the publication had not 
even been discussed at a meeting of the journalist collective." 
Besides, the proposed reorganization slates nearly 70 percent 
of journalists for dismissal. They are being offered work at 10 
new agencies to be organized on a commercial basis. As the 
journalist put it, "the charter, the list of staff members, and 
the accord with the founder -- which is the Russian Federation 
Government -- had been concealed from the collective as a 
"commercial secret" by the newspaper chiefs with its editor, 
Natalya Polezhayeva, at the head. 

</TEXT>

