<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Signs Order on Draft </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Signs Order on Draft </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604092294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0847 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1604092294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 16 TASS -- To execute Presidential 
Decree No. 784, Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev on Friday 
signed Order No. 116 on drafting Russian Federation citizens 
into military service in paril-June 1994 and transferring 
soldiers, sailors, sergeants, sergeants-major, petty officers 
and military builders who served the terms of military duty, to 
the reserve, the Defence Ministry's Directorate for Information 
and the press announced on Saturday. Under the order, subject 
to the draft are Russian Federation citizens born in 1967-1976 
who are not entitled to deferment or exemption from the draft. 

</TEXT>

