<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Launches New Destroyer in Petersburg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin Launches New Destroyer in Petersburg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704111494 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 1030 GMT 17 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] RIA reports: Russia needs a powerful, modern navy, 
Russian Federation Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin said at a 
ceremony to raise the St. Andrew's flag over the new destroyer, 
Intrepid [Besstrashnyy], to bring it into service. The 
destroyer handed over to the Russian Navy today is the first 
naval ship to be launched for two years. Viktor Chernomyrdin 
noted that the task of constructing a new Russian fleet is being 
tackled under extremely difficult conditions connected with the 
loss of a number of military bases in the Baltic, on the Black 
Sea, and the Caspian, and also with the difficult economic 
condition and the complicated political situation. 

