sees no other way forward. We have come a long way in 
implementing market transformations and one can already talk 
about certain successes, the Russian prime minister said. In 
the first place we have brought down inflation, and steadied it 
at eight or nine percent a month. 
  Chernomyrdin thanked the Western partners for taking part in 
the meeting. Taking part in the meeting on the Russian side 
were Deputy Prime Minister Aleksandr Shokhin, Central Bank 
Chairman Viktor Gerashchenko, Acting Finance Minister Sergey 
Dubinin and other officials. 

