<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Ignatyev] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg April 17 TASS--The EBRD [European 
Bank for Reconstruction and Development] will grant a 10.3 
million dollar credit to the Russian space industry which will 
be used for launching into space the European "Inmarsat" 
satellite by the Russian "Proton" booster rocket. The ceremony 
of signing this credit agreement in St. Petersburg was attended 
by Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin. 
  The EBRD President Jacques de Larosiere described this 
agreement as an important and symbolic act. He pointed out that 
the agreement is an example of integration of Russia's high 
technologies into the international market. 
  During the signing ceremony Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin described the agreement as the beginning of "a long 
road". "St. Petersburg is a window to Europe opening the way for 
our partners. We realize that much will depend on us, but we 
must create conditions to enable them to work normally," 
Chernomyrdin said. 

</TEXT>

