<H3> <TI>   Grain Procurement To Fall 1 Million Tonnes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grain Procurement To Fall 1 Million Tonnes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1604125094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 16 Apr 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> MK1604125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed ADS report: "Procurement Prices for 1994 </F>
Crops Will Be 180,000 to 200,000 Rubles Per Tonne"] 
  [Text] Procurement prices for 1994 crops will be on average 
"not less than 180,000 to 200,000 rubles [R] per tonne." In 
1993, this sum constituted R57,000. This was the conclusion 
made 14 April by the Russian Federation Government's Food 
Commission. In the current year the government will procure 
10.7 million tonnes of grain into the federal food fund designed 
to supply military and same-status categories of citizens, as 
well as for other purposes, which is 1.1 million tonnes less 
than in 1993. The government will allocate R1.6 trillion in 
budget loans to raise federal grain funds and, in addition, 5.5 
trillion to 6 trillion will be channeled for these purposes from 
the state fund to ship foodstuffs to Upper North areas. 

</TEXT>

