<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karelia: Parliament Head Elected Head of Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karelia: Parliament Head Elected Head of Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704210394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2041 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1704210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Zlobin] </F>
  [Text] Petrozavodsk April 17 TASS -- Viktor Stepanov, 
chairman of the local parliament in Russia's northwestern 
Republic of Karelia, was elected on Sunday head of the 
republic's executive branch, according to preliminary results of 
elections to Karelia's new power structures. Local observers 
believe that the post of head of government to be occupied by 
Stepanov is very similar to that of president as for its powers. 
Elections were also held to a new two-chamber local parliament, 
the Legislative Assembly. The parliament is to consist of 61 
lawmakers. Apart from this, residents in Karelia's cities, 
towns and districts voted for candidates to local governing 
bodies. 
  At the moment, election officials are counting votes at 
polling stations. According to preliminary information, the 
average turnout across the republic made up slightly over 40 per 
cent, while only 35 per cent are required for elections to be 
valid. 
  Foreign observers of Vermont, as well as representatives of 
various parties and movements said the polls were 
well-organized. No irregularities were reported. 

</TEXT>

