<DOCNO> FBIS4-16481 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov074_d_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-074 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  15 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kaliningrad To Conduct Talks With Lithuania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kaliningrad To Conduct Talks With Lithuania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1504191694 Tallinn BNS in English 1317 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1504191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kaliningrad, Russia, Apr 15, BNS -- Yuri Matochkin, 
head of the Kaliningrad region's administration, may soon be 
given full-scale authorizations to hold talks with Lithuania on 
Russia's behalf. At a press conference in Kaliningrad, 
Matochkin said such authorizations were promised at his meeting 
with Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin in Moscow this 
week. 
  Commenting on relations with Lithuania, Matochkin said 
Russia 
introduces "strict requirements" for Lithuania this year. He 
noted, however, that Russia's policy may be milder if Lithuania 
treats Kaliningrad in a more favorable way. In his words, the 
region already made its move with respect to Lithuania. 
Matochkin said "further advancement" and a more favorable trade 
status for Lithuania in the greater Russia will be possible only 
then. Matochkin said this year the region will focus on the 
development of its relations with Scandinavian and Baltic 
countries. 
  Discussing a scheduled visit to Kaliningrad April 19 by the 
German finance minister, Matochkin said the visit was arranged 
on the initiative of the German side. "We will not ask anything 
from Germans, we will only suggest," he said. "As regards 
credits, we already have three foreign credit lines for 50, 8 
and 10 million dollars," but he declined to specify any 
potential creditors. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-16482 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov074_d_94005" </HT>


<HEADER>
