<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Second Round of Ossetian-Ingush Talks Ends </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Second Round of Ossetian-Ingush Talks Ends </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504195894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1830 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1504195894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz April 15 TASS--The two-day second round 
of North Ossetian-Ingush summit negotiations ended in Nalchik 
today after discussing a draft agreement on principles, measures 
and time to implement the Russian president's decree "On 
Procedure of Return of Refugees and Forced Migrants to Places of 
Their Permanent Residence in Northern Ossetia and Ingushetia". 
  The sides have discussed the document's preamble and the 
first article. The Ossetian side suggested to have the 
following wording of the first article "The parties to the 
agreement confirm the status of the Prigorodny region as a 
territory of the North Ossetian Republic in accordance with a 
decree of the Russian president of December 13, 1993, and voice 
their refusal from any territorial claims on each other and a 
third party". 
  In the opinion of the Ingush side, the Prigorodny region 
belongs to Ingushetia as ethnic Ingushes populated the area 
before deportation. 
  A break in negotiations has been announced. The date of the 
next meeting in Nalchik will be announced later. The North 
Ossetian and Ingush working groups and experts in Vladikavkaz 
and Nazran will continue to elaborate articles of the draft 
agreement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

