<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Edict on Consultations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Edict on Consultations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604114694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1026 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1604114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 16 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin signed an edict on Friday instructing the Russian 
Government to hold consultations with representatives of the 
state authorities and all the political movements of the Chechen 
Republic to find a way out of the existing sociopolitical 
situation. 
  On the basis of these consultations, a draft treaty will be 
drawn up on demarcating areas of jurisdiction between the 
federal state authorities and the Chechen authorities and on a 
mutual delegating of powers. 

</TEXT>

