<H3> <TI>   Chechnya Prepares for Consultation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chechnya Prepares for Consultation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704164194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1342 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1704164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sharip Asuyev] </F>
  [Text] Groznyy April 17 TASS -- Chechnya praised the 
Russian leadership for seeking a peaceful solution to the social 
and political crisis in the North Caucasian republic. Chechen 
President Dzhokhar Dudayev told TASS on Sunday that his analysts 
were thoroughly studying the decree by Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin, which instructs the Russian Government to hold 
necessary consultations with the Chechen side. The republic's 
government will gather in an extraordinary meeting tonight to 
make an official return statement by the Chechen leadership. 
  The analysis of the current situation in Chechnya gives 
shows 
that the republican authorities are likely to search for a 
mutually acceptable solution to the Chechen problem [sentence as 
received]. Talks may stumble over demands that Chechnya 
recognize itself a subject of the Russian Federation, as well as 
over Russia's repeated appeals to forces in opposition to 
President Dudayev. 

</TEXT>

