<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Issues Statement on Army Neutrality </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Issues Statement on Army Neutrality </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504152394 Minsk Belarusian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information in Russian 2017 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Belarusian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The collegium of the Belarusian Defense Ministry has 
published a statement. The leadership of the armed forces 
expressed concern that the election campaign under way is being 
accompanied by an intensification of political tension around 
the Army. The statement recalls that, in accordance with the 
Constitution, servicemen enjoy civil rights and are not linked 
to decisions of political parties. According to the law "On the 
Armed Forces of the Republic of Belarus," the activity of any 
parties, sociopolitical movements, and other other organizations 
is prohibited in the Army. The collegium of the Defense Ministry 
demanded an end to attempts to draw the Army into the political 
struggle. 

</TEXT>

