<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Snegur Welcomes Ukraine Joining CIS Economic Union </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Snegur Welcomes Ukraine Joining CIS Economic Union </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504200494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1814 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1504200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Moldovan leadership intends to examine the 
memorandum on border cooperation between Russia, Ukraine and 
Belarus signed in Moscow on April 15, Moldovan President Mircea 
Snegur told Interfax before leaving Moscow. "I am not familiar 
with this memorandum. It was not discussed at the CIS summit. 
However, we must study this issue. It would be quite useful 
for us," Snegur pointed out. 
  Snegur welcomed Ukraine joining the CIS economic union as an 
associated member. "This would enhance economic cooperation 
between Ukraine and Moldova," he stressed. However, Snegur 
underlined that economic relations between Ukraine and Moldova 
were based primarily on a bilateral treaty. 

</TEXT>

