<H3> <TI>   Dniester Leader Reports to Parliament on Talks With Snegur </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dniester Leader Reports to Parliament on Talks With Snegur </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1704162494 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2028 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1704162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol, ROMPRES, 15/4/1994 -- Yesterday, 14 
April, Igor Smirnov [Dniester leader] reported to the session of 
parliament of the self-proclaimed Dniester Republic the items he 
discussed with President Snegur in their recent meeting. 
Smirnov said all problems concerning relations between Chisinau 
and Tiraspol, except the status and the terms of withdrawal of 
the 14th Army, have been discussed. Negotiations on the special 
status of Dniester will be held on the basis of suggestions of 
the CSCE mission and Russian Federation, said Smirnov, 
mentioning that the suggestions of Russia are more favorable for 
the Dniester republic. He also pleaded for the Ukraine to enter 
negotiations, mentioning that he will continue to stand for the 
confederalization of Moldova. According to the declarations of 
the leader from Tiraspol at the mentioned meeting both leaders 
accepted that Moldova cannot yet have a single currency in 
circulation. The negotiators agreed. 

</TEXT>

