<H3> <TI>   Gutsu Comments on Russian Monetary System Merge Experiment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gutsu Comments on Russian Monetary System Merge Experiment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404221694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1934 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1404221694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moldovan Vice Premier Ivan Gutsu stated that the 
merging of the Russian and Belarusian monetary systems was a 
political move rather than an economic one. He suggested in an 
interview with Interfax today that Kishinev [Chisinau] would 
follow the experiment with great interest, however, Moldova did 
not as yet intend to participate in it. Gutsu emphasized that 
Moldova would strengthen its national currency unit -- lei, the 
exchange rate of which had been stable for the last months. 
  "To have our own national currency does not harm economic 
relations between the CIS states. Moreover, after the Moldovan 
Parliament ratified the agreement on joining the CIS and the CIS 
economic union signed by Moldovan President Mircea Snegur, these 
relations will become closer. We will consider the issue on 
participation in the customs union and in the single payment 
zone," Gutsu said. 

</TEXT>

