<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Reduces Natural Gas Supply To Chisinau by 30 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Reduces Natural Gas Supply To Chisinau by 30 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1704162094 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2028 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1704162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 15/4/1994 -- Russia reduced 
the volume of natural gas supply for Moldova by 30 percent 
beginning on the afternoon of 14 April, told BASAPRESS Ion Grau, 
vice-director of the State Gas Department. The cause was 
Moldova's failure to pay the Russian "Gazprom" organization 
debts amounting to 150 billion Russian rubles, specified the 
quoted source. Ion Grau said that in order to economize 
supplies the pressure in the gas pipelines is to be reduced. 
According to Grau, many people did not pay in time for natural 
gas and that is why the debts were not repaid. Natural gas 
worth about $700,000 is consumed each day in Moldova, specified 
Grau. 

</TEXT>

