<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev's Physician Gives Further Detail of Condition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504160994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1512 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1504160994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Amangeldiy Akhmetalimov, </F>
Gennadiy Kulagin] 
  [Text] Almaty, 15 April (TASS) -- "Kazakh President 
Nursultan Nazarbayev has chronic radiculitis exacerbation," 
Nazarbayev's physician Vladimir Perekhoda told KAZTAG. This is 
the reason for his today's absence from a meeting of the 
Commonwealth councils of state and government heads. 
  "The president used to work in a foundry. He lifted heavy 
things and once overstrained himself. The trauma later 
developed into chronic radiculitis," he said. 
  "A whole group of physicians is taking care of the 
president. 
We are unanimous in the opinion that radiculitis and cold 
Nazarbayev is suffering from must be cured. That is why, we 
recommended the president to cancel his Moscow visit," stressed 
the physician. 

</TEXT>

