<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supply of Gas to Ukraine To Be Resumed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Supply of Gas to Ukraine To Be Resumed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504125694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1128 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504125694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Glazovskaya] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 15 Apr -- Saparmurat Niyazov and Leonid 
Kravchuk have expressed their mutual aspirations to overcome the 
difficulties that have arisen by taking both parties' interests 
and mutual advantage into account. The presidents of 
Turkmenistan and Ukraine met in Moscow today at the meeting of 
CIS heads of state. 
  Agreement was reached that Turkmenistan would resume the 
supply of natural gas to Ukraine from 15 April this year, since 
the Ukrainian side has found an acceptable solution for paying 
off its debts. 
  The presidents of the two countries approved an interstate 
agreement which sets out a clear schedule for the settlement of 
payments and reciprocal supplies from Ukraine. Thus, the first 
payments amounting to $10 million have already been made and the 
supply of goods and various products worth $60 million has 
begun. According to the schedule, Ukraine will make payments of 
$78 million and supply goods and various other products worth 
$200 million every quarter. 
  During their conversation, the presidents spoke in favor of 
actively continuing their dialogue and developing cooperation, 
both on a bilateral basis and within the framework of the CIS. 

</TEXT>

