<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Kravchuk Agree To Share Black Sea Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Kravchuk Agree To Share Black Sea Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1504162394 Paris AFP in English 1613 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1504162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 15 April (AFP) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin and Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk signed a deal 
Friday [15 April] to share out the disputed Black Sea Fleet on a 
50-50 basis. 
  But the agreement states Ukraine will use only between 15 
percent and 20 percent of the fleet for its own purposes and 
will lease the remainder of its share to Russia, Ukrainian 
Defence Minister Vitaliy Radetsky said at a press conference. 

</TEXT>

