<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kiev Denies Black Sea Fleet Ships Port Access </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kiev Denies Black Sea Fleet Ships Port Access </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1504093094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 15 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1504093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Viktor Yadukha from Sevastopol under the </F>
"Conflict" rubric: "Black Sea Fleet Ships Denied Access to 
Ukrainian Ports. Admiral Baltin Does Not Want To Take Any Risky 
Steps"] 
  [Text] It has transpired from sources close to the Black 
Sea Fleet staff that a telegram from Ukrainian Defense Minister 
General Vitaliy Radetskyy to Admiral Eduard Baltin, Black Sea 
Fleet commander, was received on 15 April, in which the former 
categorically objects to the entry of Black Sea Fleet ships and 
vessels to the Ukrainian ports of Odessa, Izmail, Kherson, and 
Nikolayev. Meanwhile, the Black Sea Fleet command has been 
preparing ships for evacuating eight families of the 318th 
Division's servicemen who refused to take the oath of loyalty to 
Ukraine. When meeting with them, Vice Admiral Vladimir 
Beskaravaynyy, commander in chief of the Ukrainian Navy, who 
heads the naval field staff at the "Slavutich" cruiser in 
Odessa, proposed that the officers take an oath of allegiance to 
Ukraine and follow him on board "Slavutich." The commander of 
"Ilya Azarov," a ship blocked in the Odessa port, responded: 
"We will not go to an enemy ship; these people have robbed us. 
They will finish robbing us there." 
  In Odessa, the Black Sea Fleet's surveillance post has also 
been blocked. Black Sea Fleet staff officers point out that the 
Ukrainian Defense Ministry has made it clear by its actions that 
it is carrying out the functions of the Ukrainian Supreme Soviet 
and its Foreign Ministry. 
  Currently, the 318th Division of mothballed ships includes 
three Black Sea Fleet ships, on which Ukrainian flags have 
already been hoisted. Black Sea Fleet Commander Adm. Baltin has 
decided not to take any steps to evacuate servicemen, because 
this may be interpreted by the Ukrainian side as a provocation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

