<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alternative Ukrainian Black Sea Fleet Commanders Appointed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Alternative Ukrainian Black Sea Fleet Commanders Appointed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1604090094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 16 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1604090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Konstantin Parishkura from Kiev under the general </F>
heading: "Ukraine Has Decided To Play War With the Black Sea 
Fleet. Meanwhile, Yeltsin and Kravchuk Have Decided To Split the 
Fleet"] 
  [Text] Meanwhile, on 15 April the press center of the 
Ukrainian Defense Ministry issued the following statement: 
"Vice Admiral Vladimir Beskorovaynyy, commander in chief of the 
Ukrainian Navy, has said that in accordance with the Ukrainian 
Naval organization plan, the creation of the Western Sea Area 
under Captain First Rank Dmitriy Ukrainets continues. Today, 
commanders of Black Sea Fleet units in Izmail, Ochakov, and 
Nikolayev will be introduced to their Ukrainian counterparts so 
as to organize cooperation. Military formations, command and 
control agencies, and their staffs are being set up in advance 
so that they will grow into the situation in the areas and 
prepare for taking over ships after the problem of splitting the 
Black Sea Fleet is resolved. The newly created formations will 
be tasked with interfering in the activity of the existing Black 
Sea Fleet units. [as published] 

</TEXT>

