<H3> <TI>   Churkin Achieves `Serious Basis' for Bosnian Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Churkin Achieves `Serious Basis' for Bosnian Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504183494 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1700 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504183494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Remarks by Vitaliy Churkin, Russian special envoy and </F>
deputy foreign minister, to correspondents on 15 April; place 
not given; from the "Novosti" newscast--recorded] 
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] Our talks in Belgrade were 
centered on the difficult problem of concluding an all-embracing 
agreement on cessation of all hostilities between the Serbs and 
the Muslims in all the territories of Bosnia-Herzegovina. There 
were three extensive, serious, and constructive conversations 
with Serbian President Milosevic. We continued our contacts 
with the leaders [words indistinct]. It is not without 
satisfaction that I can now say that, in my view, I have a 
serious basis for concluding such an agreement. It envisages 
disengagement of the fighting sides; in other words, it will be 
a real agreement on ending the war in Bosnia-Herzegovina and not 
just another declaration on ceasing hostilities. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

