<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Calls For Gorazde Demilitarized Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calls For Gorazde Demilitarized Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604200794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1930 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1604200794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Naryshkin] </F>
  [Text] Zagreb April 16 TASS -- Russian envoy Vitaliy 
Churkin has called for establishing a demilitarised zone around 
Gorazde similar to that in Sarajevo, Sarajevo television said on 
Saturday. 
  Churkin said that this would involve the withdrawal of heavy 
artillery from the 20-kilometer security zone around the city 
and deployment of U.N. peace-keeping troops in the region. 
"This is the only way out of the current chaos," he said. 
  Bosnia-Herzegovina's leaders Alija Izetbegovic and Haris 
Silajdzic demanded at a meeting with U.N. envoy Yasushi Akashi 
guarantees of immediate cease-fire around Gorazde. Otherwise 
Akashi should guarantee that Serb positions will be subjected to 
"energetic air strikes," Izetbegovic said. 

</TEXT>

