<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Discuss Gorazde Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Discuss Gorazde Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704151094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1430 GMT 
17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yasushi Akashi and Vitaliy Churkin, special envoys 
of the UN secretary general and the Russian president, held 
talks with the leader of the Bosnian Serbs Radovan Karadzic in 
the Sarajevo suburb of Pale today. This was the first meeting 
between Akashi and Karadzic since NATO planes bombed Serb 
positions near Gorazde a week ago. 
  An ITAR-TASS correspondent has learned at the Zagreb 
headquarters of peacekeeping forces that at the Pale meeting 
they discussed conditions for a cease-fire under which Bosnian 
Serbs could suspend their offensive on Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

