<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Comments on Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Comments on Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504171494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1637 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1504171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 15 Apr--"Accords on the division of the 
Russian and Ukrainian Navies based on the shores of the Black 
Sea coast will be reached within 10 days." Ukrainian President 
Leonid Kravchuk said this after the conclusion of talks held 
today between the Russian and Ukrainian delegations at the 
President Hotel in Moscow. 
  According to Kravchuk, the two sides "have instructed the 
Foreign Ministries to begin preparing a full-scale treaty 
between Russia and Ukraine." He said that "a protocol stating 
the intention of the two countries to cooperate in the 
military-technological sphere was signed by them for the first 
time". 
  Kravchuk also said that the question of the resignation of 
Black Sea Fleet Commander [Eduard] Baltin had not been discussed 
but that "the Ukrainian side did not insist, as a matter of 
principle, on his resignation at the talks that took place." 
Kravchuk said that accords had been reached with regard to the 
location of the two countries' naval forces and that their 
parameters had been established in percentage terms. 
  Summing up today's talks, he added: "There are no issues 
between Ukraine and Russia that we are unable to resolve. We 
have fully resolved all problems that existed in our bilateral 
relations." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

