<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Says Iraq Incident Must Be Investigated </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Says Iraq Incident Must Be Investigated </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504192894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1814 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1504192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A high-ranking official from the Russian Foreign 
Ministry stressed that Moscow had given consideration to the 
tragic incident in northern Iraq where two U.S. fighters had 
erroneously shot down two helicopters carrying UN 
representatives. "We would like to express our deep regret and 
our condolences to the relatives and friends of those who died," 
the diplomat said in an interview with Interfax today. 
  "However, the incident has caused us serious concern since 
this happened in the so-called no flight zone in Iraqi 
Kurdistan, to the north of the 32nd parallel, controlled by the 
"coalition deterrence forces" consisting of air units of the 
Western participants in the anti-Iraqi coalition, the activities 
of which were not defined by appropriate international 
decisions," the Russian diplomat emphasized. 
  He said the world community should expect careful and 
impartial investigations into this tragic incident and to be 
informed on all the details of it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

