<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Seeks Intensified Russian Role in Middle East </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Seeks Intensified Russian Role in Middle East </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804102794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat, who arrives in Moscow 
today for talks with the Russian leadership, hopes to reach 
agreement on intensifying Russian mediation in the Middle East 
settlement, a high-ranking representative of the Palestinian 
embassy in Moscow told a RIA correspondent. He said that the 
PLO head hopes that Russia could play the main role in the 
resumption of the bilateral Palestinian-Israeli talks on Gaza 
and Jericho, broken off as a result of the tragic events in 
Hebron. The Russian Foreign Ministry told RIA that 'Arafat's 
visit will last until 20 April. The itinerary envisions talks 
with the leadership of the foreign policy department, meetings 
with State Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin, Internal Affairs Minister 
Viktor Yerin, and also with Aleksey II, patriarch of All Russia. 

</TEXT>

