<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Meets With G-7 Delegations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin Meets With G-7 Delegations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704165594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1531 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1704165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg April 17 TASS -- Russian Prime 
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin met here on Sunday with delegations 
of the Group-of-Seven highly industrialized countries and 
international financial organizations. 
  Participants in the closed-door meeting discussed 
coordination of international assistance to Russian reforms, 
specifically the possibility of creating a multilateral agency 
to insure foreign investments against non-commercial risks. 
  Chernomyrdin told the gathering that the Russian leadership 
was firmly committed to the course of reforms. "We have 
advanced considerably in market-oriented transformations and can 
now speak about certain progress on this way", the Russian prime 
minister emphasised. Among the most significant achievements, 
he listed the bringing of inflation down to 8-9 per cent a month. 
  Chernomyrdin thanked Western partners for their 
participation 
in the meeting. 
  Russia was represented at the meeting by Deputy Prime 
Minister Aleksandr Shokhin, Central Bank Chief Viktor 
Gerashchenko, Acting Finance Minister Sergey Dubinin and other 
officials. 

</TEXT>

