<H3> <TI>   Meshkov Issues Decrees Introducing `Open Economy' in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meshkov Issues Decrees Introducing `Open Economy' in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1504132994 Kiev KIEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI in Russian 14 Apr 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> WS1504132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev KIEVSKIYE VEDOMOSTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Irina Titova: "There Is a New Regime in the </F>
Crimea. Open Economy."] 
  [Text] Some sensational information was disclosed 
yesterday at the Ukrainian National Entrepreneurship Assembly 
session. Oleksandr Dudko, chairman of the Crimean Union of 
Industrialists and Entrepreneurs, presented three decrees signed 
by Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov, all of which bore the date 
of signing, registration numbers, and, as it was put, still-wet 
ink. Practically, this means that the Crimea has entered a new 
economic era, something that industrialists and entrepreneurs 
have been trying to obtain from the government for several long 
months. The documents signed by Yuriy Meshkov implemented the 
23 June decree of Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk, "On Open 
Economic Regime in the Territory of the Crimean Republic." 

</TEXT>

