<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Disagreement With Abkhazia on Peacekeeper Deployment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Disagreement With Abkhazia on Peacekeeper Deployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1504200094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1824 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1504200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Konstantin Pribytkov] </F>
  [Text] Geneva April 15 TASS -- Delegations from Georgia and 
its separatist province of Abkhazia failed to reach a compromise 
on where to deploy UN peacekeepers. 
  The UN- and Russia-brokered four-day talks were held in 
accordance with accords signed in Moscow early in April. 
  The sides remained adamant in their approach to a proposed 
stationing of the UN peacekeepers. Abkhazia suggests they must 
be deployed along the border river of Inguri, while Georgia says 
peacekeepers should control the whole territory of the breakaway 
province. 

</TEXT>

