<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Landsbergis Rebuked for Statement at Council of Europe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Landsbergis Rebuked for Statement at Council of Europe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604091394 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
0600 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1604091394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lithuanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During the visit by Lithuanian President Algirdas 
Brazauskas to the Council of Europe, a statement by Vytautas 
Landsbergis, a member of the Seimas delegation to the 
parliamentary assembly of the Council of Europe on Russia's 
intention to join the Council of Europe was distributed among 
the parliamentarians of this organization. 
  In this statement, the Lithuanian Foreign Ministry is 
accused 
of conducting a policy based on Moscow's directives, reads a 
statement by this ministry, disseminated by its information and 
press department. 
  The Ministry of Foreign Affairs does not discuss the 
accusation, which is not based on any arguments, and stresses 
that such statements, which had more than once been publicly 
distributed abroad, harm the prestige of the Lithuanian state. 
  Lithuania's stance on Russia's membership in the Council of 
Europe is based on the following principles: 
  Russia must fulfill the conditions of the Council of Europe 
on the membership in that organization; 
  Lithuania will support Russia's membership in the Council of 
Europe only after Russia fulfills international obligations on 
the withdrawal of troops from Latvia and Estonia, respects the 
sovereignty of the neighboring states, human rights, and those 
of national minorities; 
  The support of the Council of Europe to Russia's democratic 
forces is a weighty contribution to the processes of 
democratization and the development of reforms in that country, 
says this statement in conclusion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

