<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Cooperation Pact Initialed With Romanian Diplomat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Cooperation Pact Initialed With Romanian Diplomat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1504110494 Tallinn BNS in English 0914 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1504110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] RIGA, Apr 14, BNS - Latvian Foreign Ministry's 
Iveta Sers and Romanian diplomat Dan Tiron initialed an 
agreement Thursday [14 April] on trade and economic relations 
between both countries. 
  The draft agreement provides for the most favored nation 
status in mutual trade, the Latvian Foreign Ministry said. 
  The trade agreement should be ratified and enter into force 
until summer. 
  Latvia has already signed similar agreements with the United 
States, Australia, Austria, Belgium, the Czech Republic, 
Denmark, France, Greece, Italy, India, Iceland, Ireland, Great 
Britain, Luxembourg, the Netherlands, Portugal, Poland, Spain, 
Hungary and Germany, as well as with several CIS countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

