<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Frontier Guard Brigade Gets New Commander </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Frontier Guard Brigade Gets New Commander </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1504185394 Tallinn BNS in English 1502 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1504185394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Apr 15, BNS -- Latvian Defense Minister 
Valdis Pavlovskis appointed Captain Janis Adamsons as commander 
of the country's Frontier Guard Brigade, the Defense Ministry 
reports. 
  Adamsons has been deputy commander of Latvia's Naval Forces 
since June 15, 1992. 
  Adamsons was born in 1956 at Livani, graduated from Kiev 
(Ukraine) naval school in 1979, served in various units of the 
Soviet Naval Border Guards. 
  As reported, the former commander of border guards, Ivars 
Redisons, resigned in the end of March. His duties were 
performed by acting commander, former deputy commander Viktors 
Sviklis, until the appointment of Adamsons. 

</TEXT>

