<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chinese Prime Minister Arrives on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chinese Prime Minister Arrives on Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804160194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1528 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804160194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tashkent 18 April, TASS -- Thousands of residents of 
Tashkent spilled into the streets of the city to welcome Chinese 
Prime Minister Li Peng who arrived in Uzbekistan on an official 
visit on Monday. 
  At Tashkent's Airport Li Peng observed the guard of honour. 
The national anthems of the two countries were played. 
  "I am glad that I am here, in this ancient and world-known 
city of Tashkent," Li Peng said. "The visit by President Islam 
Karimov of Uzbekistan to our country in 1992 opened a new page 
in the history of friendly relations between our countries," he 
continued. 
  The Chinese premier expressed the hope that "the documents 
to 
be signed during the visit will strengthen friendly ties and 
elevate our economic cooperation to a new height." 
  Karimov stressed that Li Peng's visit is taking place at a 
time when political, economic, trade and cultural ties between 
the two countries are growing ever stronger. He expressed the 
confidence that the visit will become a new step towards 
strengthening relations between Uzbekistan and China. "Friendly 
ties between our states date back to the time of the 'great silk 
route,'" he said. 
  This is the first visit to Uzbekistan by the Chinese prime 
minister. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

