<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suleymenov: Baykonur Dispute With Russia Resolved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Suleymenov: Baykonur Dispute With Russia Resolved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804150294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1318 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia and Kazakhstan have reached agreement on the 
Baykonur satellite-launching site, Kazakhstan's foreign minister 
said. What remains to be clarified are some "technical" points, 
Tuleutay Suleymenov told INTERFAX. 
  He said Kazakhstan President Nursultan Nazarbayev, had 
recently put his signature to a Kazakh-Russian memorandum on 
Baykonur. 
  Suleymenov said Kazakhstan is to lease the site to Russia 
for 
$118 million a year. Leninsk town, forming part of the Baykonur 
complex, is to be governed jointly by the two countries, he 
said. "Baykonur and Leninsk are on the territory of Kazakhstan 
and must be used jointly," he said. 

</TEXT>

