<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Parliament Session Begins 18 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Parliament Session Begins 18 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Nazarbayev Speaks </H4>

<F P=102> LD1804162394 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, a meeting was held in Almaty of 
representatives of Supreme Kenges deputies from all the regions 
of the Republic. At the request of the parliamentarians, 
President Nazarbayev took part and spoke to the deputies. He 
congratulated the people's deputies on the high confidence in 
them and wished them every success in their work. 
  The head of state shared his opinion on the nature of the 
work and activity expected from the Supreme Kenges of the new 
convocation. He expressed his hope that from the very beginning 
the first ever democratically elected professional parliament 
will work constructively in the interest of the state and for 
the whole Kazakh nation. The president stated his readiness to 
work in a close, concerted, and efficient way with the Supreme 
Kenges in order to lift our society out of the crisis as quickly 
as possible and to pave the way toward a civilized future. 
  Nursultan Nazarbayev believes that the Kazakhstani 
parliamentarians have every possibility to formulate their own 
specific style of law-making, which will take into account the 
particular features of our Republic, in particular its 
multiethnic population. He also answered deputies' questions. 
At issue were proposals regarding an initiative deputy group on 
how to begin the first session of the Supreme Kenges in an 
organized way. The proposals were approved in general. 
  On the same day, at the House of parliament, Central 
Election 
Commission Chairman Karatay Turysov awarded the deputies their 
newly designed badges. The session will open tomorrow at 1000. 

</TEXT>

