<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hryb Comments on Amending Constitution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hryb Comments on Amending Constitution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1804144494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1200 
GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1804144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, legislative speaker Mechyslaw Hryb and Head 
of the CIS Executive Secretariat Ivan Karatchenya held a news 
conference at the Supreme Soviet of the Republic of Belarus, 
dedicated to the results of the regular conference of the CIS 
heads of state and government, held in Moscow last week. 
Mechyslaw Hryb told those present about the conference and 
voiced satisfaction over its results. In particular, he pointed 
out that 26 issues were addressed and as many documents signed. 
They were on the implementation of the treaty on the forming of 
the economic union, the realization of commissions issued by the 
Heads of State Council, the issues discussed at the initiative 
of states, statutory, and branch bodies of the Commonwealth, and 
so on. 
  The Supreme Soviet chairman answered reporters questions 
about the agreement signed between the Government of the Russian 
Federation and the Republic of Belarus on the unification of 
monetary systems. The legislative speaker said that he was not 
an advocate of amending the Constitution and has no right to do 
this. This can be resolved solely by the Supreme Soviet. 

</TEXT>

