<H3> <TI>   More on Kebich Remarks on Union With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on Kebich Remarks on Union With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1804133994 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 16 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM1804133994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Oleg Stepanenko: "Vyacheslav Kebich: I Have Not </F>
Sold Belarus Out"] 
  [Text] Minsk -- Before leaving for the meeting of heads of 
state and government in Moscow, Vyacheslav Kebich, chairman of 
the Belarus Council of Ministers, held a press conference for 
local and foreign correspondents devoted to the agreement 
concluded 12 April on unifying the Belorussian [Belarusian] and 
Russian monetary systems. 
  "As far as the accusations that I have sold out Belarus or 
handed it over to somebody are concerned, I can state officially 
yet again that I made my choice and have no regrets. This was 
the choice of my life, and I am prepared to sacrifice everything 
to see it all through to the finish, since I am profoundly 
convinced that union [soyuz] with Russia will be our salvation 
and our children's salvation." 
  The prime minister talked in detail about how the agreement 
had come about. The work began two years ago, he noted, but it 
has been particularly intensive for the past eight months. The 
Belorussian side submitted 30 versions of the agreement during 
this period. Vigorous opposition from certain forces within both 
Belorussia and Russia had to be overcome. 
  As PRAVDA has already reported, the agreement is in two 
parts. The first applies to the unification of monetary systems, 
while the second applies to matters with a direct bearing on 
customs operations, duties, and the status of Russian troops on 
Belorussian territory. The articles in part two of the 
agreement, which envisage the lifting of trade duties and 
payments to allow Russian goods to transit Belorussian territory 
or to allow the Russian side to lease strategic installations, 
come into force 26 April. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

