<H3> <TI>   Signs Cooperation Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Signs Cooperation Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804202194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1803 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804202194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today Moldovan President Mircea Snegur and Chief of 
the Russian Service of Foreign Intelligence, Yevgeniy Primakov, 
signed an agreement in Kishinev [Chisinau] on cooperation 
between the Moldovan National Security Ministry and the Russian 
Service of Foreign Intelligence in the sphere of struggle with 
terrorism, organized crime, drugs and illegal arms traffic. 
  After the signing Snegur told journalists that the present 
socio-political situation in Moldova was favorable for the 
settlement of the armed conflict in Transdniestria which started 
in 1992. 
  Primakov stressed that the approach displayed by the 
Moldovan 
leadership when seeking a peace settlement was a good example 
for former Soviet republics plagued by armed conflicts. 

</TEXT>

