<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimea Urges CIS To Support Deportees' Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimea Urges CIS To Support Deportees' Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804134394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1313 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Lev Ryabchikov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol 18 April, TASS -- Crimean President Yuriy 
Meshkov and Vice-Prime Minister Yevgeniy Saburov called on the 
CIS leaders to support the return of the deported people of the 
Republic. 
  In an appeal issued on the eve of the 50th anniversary of 
the 
deportation of Crimean Tatars, Armenians, Bulgarians, Greeks and 
Germans from the Crimea, they stressed that the disintegration 
of the Soviet Union and the emergence of new independent states 
have complicated their return to their homeland. 
  Ukraine cannot finance the programme alone, the appeal said. 
Meshkov and Saburov called on the CIS presidents and governments 
to support the programme and help restore the rights of the 
deported people. 

</TEXT>

