<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk May Call Referendum on President's Authority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk May Call Referendum on President's Authority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804173294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1613 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804173294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A senior member of Ukrainian President Leonid 
Kravchuk's staff said Kravchuk's possible decision to put the 
extent of his authority before a national referendum would be 
"logical" and "absolutely constitutional." 
  "Since parliament has not solved the problem of presidential 
powers, Kravchuk will appeal to the people," Nikolay 
Mikhalchenko told INTERFAX on Monday. 
  Earlier Kravchuk said he would not stand for the next term 
of 
presidency in the June 26 elections because the future 
president's powers had not yet been delineated. Last month, 
parliament passed a law, which would give local councils to be 
elected on June 26 all executive authority in their respective 
regions and would dismiss regional presidential envoys. 
Kravchuk believes the president would then effectively cease to 
be head of the Executive Branch. 

</TEXT>

