<H3> <TI>   Grachev Favors Uniting CIS Armed Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev Favors Uniting CIS Armed Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804133394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1026 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia's Defense Minister Pavel Grachev supports the 
idea of uniting the CIS armed forces. He believes that this 
question may be discussed at the end of the year. 
  He told Interfax that after the creation of joint armed 
forces one could then talk about the formation of a CIS defense 
union. "This is something far more significant than the 
collective security agreement," he said. 
  He noted that the military tackle not only tactical but also 
strategic problems. "Our strategic future lies in a joint armed 
forces and a defense union," said Grachev. 

</TEXT>

