<H3> <TI>   Saratov-Moscow Gas Pipeline Blows Up </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saratov-Moscow Gas Pipeline Blows Up </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804130994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1026 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On Sunday night, the gas pipeline linking Saratov 
and Moscow blew up three kilometers east of the city of 
Lukhovitsy. The Ministry for Emergency Situations told Interfax 
that the explosion had occurred and a fire flared up as a result 
of the pipeline break. Gas has been switched off. No one was 
injured. Consumers are receiving gas from other pipelines. 
Repair work is underway. 

</TEXT>

