<H3> <TI>   Gunmen Attack New Russian Party Headquarters </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gunmen Attack New Russian Party Headquarters </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804165294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1608 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By CRIME-PRESS correspondent Olga Solodova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 18 TASS -- A group of unidentified 
gunmen burst on Sunday into headquarters of Russia's newly-born 
Party of Scientific and Technical Intelligentsia (PNTI) and 
sprayed the ceiling with automatic gun fire from two 
Kalashnikovs, the party press service told CRIME-PRESS on 
Monday. At the same time, another group of intruders robbed a 
money exchange office which was located next door. 
  Party leader Aleksandr Krasnov is sure it was a mock 
robbery, 
since only 2,000 roubles (about one dollar) were stolen, while 
the real aim of the break-in was to scare party-members. Last 
fall, Krasnov, a scientist and former chairman of the Moscow 
Krasnopresnenskiy District Soviet, reportedly supported the 
dissolved parliament in its stand-off with President Boris 
Yeltsin. 

</TEXT>

