<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Kharchenko] </F>
  [Text] Tver April 19 TASS -- One of the main tasks of the 
party "Russia's Choice" is to protect Russian-speaking 
population in former republics of the erstwhile Soviet Union, 
its leader Yegor Gaydar told ITAR-TASS today. For this purpose 
"we will use all levers we have, and, in particular, create 
public opinion aiemd at the protection of the Russian people who 
are subjected to oppressions by anyone," Gaydar said. 
  Yegor Gaydar eneed his tour of the Tver region today during 
which he met supporters of the" Russia's Choice" party, 
representatives of business circles and directors of enteprises 
of the Upper Volga region. 

