<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Union Leadership Under Fire at Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Union Leadership Under Fire at Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1804132594 Moscow TRUD in Russian 16 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1804132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow TRUD </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Fedor Yemchenko report under the "Such News" rubric: </F>
"FITUR: Criticism from Left and Right"] 
  [Text] An all-Russia conference of trade union committee 
chairmen has been held at the FITUR [Federation of Independent 
Trade Unions of Russia]. Those who are directly responsible for 
resolving the socioeconomic problems of labor collectives 
gathered for the representative forum. 
  Analyzing the working people's present situation, the trade 
union leaders attempted to formulate a unified strategy to 
protect the working people's interests. All the speakers 
emphasized that this can be achieved only by pooling the efforts 
of all trade union organizations. At the conference there was 
criticism of the FITUR leadership and accusations of its 
excessive politeness [loyalnost] in relations with power 
structures. 
  Representatives of Working Moscow set up their picket 
outside 
the FITUR building yesterday. The pickets accuse the FITUR 
leadership of infringing the working people's interests with the 
General Agreement between the government, employers, and trade 
unions, which they signed recently. 

</TEXT>

