<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Interfax has been informed by reliable sources in 
Russia's Foreign Ministry that the Russian president's special 
envoy Vitaliy Churkin is expected to return to Moscow from the 
troubled areas of former Yugoslavia within the next few hours. 
  The sources said that the situation in Bosnia was now 
critical. "There are only two options -- peace talks and an end 
to hostilities or a gamble on force and unending hostilities," 
one Russian diplomat said. 
  Another ministry official told Interfax that "much, if not 
everything, will depend on the position of the Bosnian and 
Belgrade Serbs." "Regrettably, it is so far clear only that the 
Serbs are not fulfilling their commitments or putting words into 
action," he stressed. 

