<H3> <TI>   Moscow To Send 600 Paratroopers to Balkans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow To Send 600 Paratroopers to Balkans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1804165094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1515 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> PM1804165094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 18 TASS -- A group of 200 Russian 
paratroopers will leave Ryazan on a peacemaking mission to the 
Balkans on Tuesday. 
  They will replace their colleagues who will return home 
after 
the end of the term of service in the U.N. peace-keeping 
contingent in the former Yugoslavia. 
  They are the first group of a contingent of 600 soldiers who 
will be flown to the region, Igor Kashin, spokesman for the 
Russian airborne troops, said on Monday. 
  He said 400 of them will be deployed in Serb Krajina and the 
rest in Sarajevo. 
  All of them are volunteers drawn on a contract basis for six 
months. 

</TEXT>

