<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Russia's Role in Middle East </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discusses Russia's Role in Middle East </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804132994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1100 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] PLO Executive Committee Chairman Yasir 'Arafat 
begins an official visit to Moscow on 19 April. On the eve of 
his visit, Yasir 'Arafat gave an exclusive interview to a 
correspondent for our information agency at the PLO headquarters 
in Tunis: 
  [Begin 'Arafat recording in Arabic with superimposed Russian 
translation] Russia has played an active role in the Near East 
peace process ever since it started. The Russian foreign 
minister and the U.S. secretary of state stood alongside myself 
and the Israeli prime minister when the Washington agreement on 
the principles of a settlement was signed. 
  It was precisely thanks to the recent increase in Russian 
diplomatic activity, Yasir 'Arafat continues, that certain 
difficulties which arose in the negotiating process were 
overcome, allowing it to resume in Cairo. The peace talks are 
being held not just in the interests of the Palestinians or the 
Israelis. They are in the interests of all mankind. Realizing 
this, and undertaking efforts in this direction, we have 
achieved those results which only became possible because of the 
peace talks. [end recording] 
  [Correspondent] To conclude his short interview, Yasir 
'Arafat noted that there has been a durable and friendly 
relationship between Palestinians and Russia for many years now. 
But in looking ahead he would like to point out that in future 
there could be new developments in this relationship because of 
the possibility of cooperation in the repair of infrastructure 
in the Palestinian autonomous areas, the training of personnel, 
and other spheres. 
  He takes this opportunity to pass on the warmest and most 
sincere greetings to the peoples of Russia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

