<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets With Rybkin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With Rybkin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904081694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0716 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904081694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 19 Apr -- State Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin 
today met with PLO Executive Committee Chairman Yasir 'Arafat. 
During the meeting, Yasir 'Arafat expressed confidence that the 
Russian side will render necessary assistance in implementing 
the recent agreements between the PLO and Israel, of which 
Russia and the United States are cosponsors. At the same time, 
Yasir 'Arafat noted that there have been recent "attempts to 
depart from the agreement and to push the Russian Federation to 
the sidelines in this process." 
  For his part, Ivan Rybkin told journalists after the meeting 
that "the Russian side favors the unconditional implementation 
of all UN Security Council resolutions concerning a peace 
settlement in the Middle East." The State Duma chairman said he 
hopes the agreement between the PLO and Israel "will be 
implemented without double standards." "I hope the last Israeli 
soldier will soon leave the occupied territories and free 
parliamentary elections will take place there to which the Duma 
will send its observers," Ivan Rybkin said. 

</TEXT>

