<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets With Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With Yeltsin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904124794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1216 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 19 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin met visiting PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat in the Grand 
Kremlin Palace today. 
  Welcoming the PLO chairman, Yeltsin said that Russia "is 
making efforts to support you politically, especially now that a 
negotiating process between PLO and Israel has begun." The 
Russian president pointed out that "our position alongside the 
position of the United States is very important". 
  Yeltsin pointed out that Russia understands PLO claims to 
Israel. In his opinion, after the meeting the negotiating 
process will go ahead more successfully. Yeltsin pointed out, 
in particular, that "we had invited Israeli Prime Minister 
Yitzhaq Rabin to visit Moscow next week" so as to avoid a break 
in the talks. 
  The meeting was attended by Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev and presidential aide for international affairs, Dmitriy 
Ryurikov. 

</TEXT>

