<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 18 April, TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin urged on Monday overcoming the deadlock in Russia's 
relations with its independence-seeking republic of Chechnya. 
  The president entrusted the government to hold consultations 
with representatives of Chechnya's state bodies as well as all 
its political movements, and basing on the results of these 
consultations, to draft a powers-sharing treaty between Moscow 
and Groznyy, the press service of the Russian president reported 
on Monday. 

