<F P=106> [Report from roundup of ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA and ITAR-TASS </F>
reports: "`Niva' With Altay Engine"] 
  [Text] The "Rostselmash" plant has completed the 
readjustment of production for the output of "Niva" grain 
harvesting combines with engines from the Barnaul "Altaydizel" 
joint-stock company. 
  Previously the "Niva" was produced only with engines from 
the 
Kharkov "Hammer and Sickle" plant. But the Ukrainian enterprise 
has shown itself to be a not entirely reliable partner and the 
complication of tax procedures when crossing the border between 
Russia and Ukraine has aggravated the problem. 

</TEXT>

