<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Agreement on Delivery of Ukrainian Jets to Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Agreement on Delivery of Ukrainian Jets to Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1804113994 Moscow Russian Television and Dubl Networks in 
Russian 0000 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1804113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television and Dubl Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Aty-Baty" program] </F>
  [Text] Petr Deynekin, commander in chief of the Russian 
Federation Air Force, has reported that no mutually acceptable 
agreement on delivery of the strategic bombers deployed on 
Ukrainian territory to Russia has yet been achieved. He 
remarked that there are currently 42 strategic missile planes, 
of which 19 are TU-160 and 23 TU-95-MS. According to him, the 
stumbling block is the astronomical sum demanded by Ukraine for 
transferring the bombers. Ukraine wants 700 billion rubles of 
its debt to Russia deducted for its delivering the planes. 
According to Russia, this sum amounts to about 200 billion 
rubles. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

