<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenian Government Delegation Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Government Delegation Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804170994 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1500 
GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804170994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] CONTACT news agency has supplied us with information 
from the press service of the Georgian cabinet of ministers that 
an Armenian Government delegation arrived today on a working 
visit in Tbilisi. The delegation is led by Armenian State 
Minister Gagik Martirosyan. The delegation was met at the 
airport by Deputy Prime Minister Irakli Menagharishvili. 
  A meting was held at the cabinet of ministers where the 
issues of securing the railways, oil and natural gas supplies, 
and the situation in trade and economy were discussed. 
  The Armenian delegation expressed its discontent over 
Saknavtobprodukti [Georgian oil products]. It was noted that in 
an immediate future, a north Caucasus-Transcaucasus gas pipeline 
would soon be put in operation, which would enhance gas supplies 
two-fold both to Georgia and Armenia. Martirosyan said that a 
group of the Armenian Government delegation had left for Batumi 
to monitor the transportation of cargo and humanitarian aid 
destined for Armenia. 
  The members of the Armenian Government delegation will 
continue work in the appropriate ministries and departments. 

</TEXT>

