<H3> <TI>   Chechen Republic To Talk Only Through Ministry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chechen Republic To Talk Only Through Ministry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804142794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1340 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Chechen Republic will hold talks with Russia 
only through the Foreign Ministry. INTERFAX correspondents 
report that this decision was taken at the session of the 
Chechen Government on Friday [15 April]. 
  In an interview with INTERFAX the Chechen president's aide 
Soltmurat Apazov said that this means raising the status of 
talks to the level of inter-state ones. According to the Chechen 
president Djokhar Dudayev, the step was taken to regulate the 
relationships between the two states. As it has become known to 
Interfax, the matter was discussed in telephone talks between 
the Dudayev and his representative in Moscow. This emphasizes 
the fact, said Dudayev, that the Chechen Republic does not 
consider itself the subject of the Russian Federation. 

</TEXT>

