<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Meets European Union Representatives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze Meets European Union Representatives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804213294 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1950 
GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804213294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The head of state's press secretariat has stated 
that Head of State Eduard Shevardnadze today met Mr. Bosham, an 
adviser from the European Union. The conversation centered on 
the complex situation of the Georgian economy and solutions to 
this problem. 
  The head of state mentioned that the situation in Georgia is 
so grave that a specific social solution has to be found. There 
are acute problems in power engineering and grain supplies; 
inflation is rising. Therefore, regulating solely the tax 
system will not resolve all the problems provided the rest of 
the issues are settled, to which end the efforts of the supreme 
authorities are directed [sentence as heard]. 
  Mr. Boshman agreed with the head of state and said that it 
is time realistic actions are carried out in order to get out of 
the situation, all the more when east European countries have 
had an experience of it. 

</TEXT>

