<H3> <TI>   Russian Version of Fleet Accord Rejected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Version of Fleet Accord Rejected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1804125194 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 15 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1804125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report on the "Statement by Ukraine's Ministry of Foreign </F>
Affairs"] 
  [Text] In connection with the 13 April information carried 
by "Ostankino" (in the "News" program) to the effect that, 
during the negotiations in Kiev, an accord was allegedly reached 
that the sides would resolve the Black Sea Fleet problems based 
on the Massandra Protocol, Ukraine's Ministry of Foreign Affairs 
contends that this does not correspond to reality. Ukraine 
proceeds from the need for a comprehensive approach toward the 
issue of the Black Sea Fleet, taking into account the 
regulations of the Dagomys, Yalta, and Zavidovo Accords, as well 
as of the Massandra Protocol. Nor does the "Ostankino" 
information on the visit to Odessa by a delegation of the 
Russian Federation correspond to reality. 
  Contrary to the accords reached in Kiev, the commander in 
chief of the Russian Navy. S. Gromov, wrecked the meeting with 
the command and officers' personnel of the Black Sea Fleet, a 
meeting that had been planned jointly with the Ukrainian side. 
Such information and actions show who places obstacles to a 
just resolution of the Black Sea Fleet problem. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

