<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coup Plotter Trial Case Transferred </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coup Plotter Trial Case Transferred </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004045294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0430 GMT 
20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004045294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The case of the State Committee for the State of 
Emergency [SCSE] has been transferred for further consideration 
to General of Justice Viktor Yaskin, judge of the Russian 
Supreme Court. The Russian legislation allows only 28 days for 
a judge to come up with a decision - in this case, either to 
resume the court trial of the SCSE or to abort it and close this 
trial for good. 

</TEXT>

